---
import tags from '../data/tags.json';
---
<style>
  article {
    margin: 40px 0 20px;
  }

  .about {
    font-size: 14px;
    margin: 10px 0;
  }

  .tags {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  
  .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 2px 4px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 2px #00000054;
  }
  

  .links {
    margin-top: 20px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 15px;
  }

  .icon {
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .icon:hover {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  hr {
    margin: 20px 0;
    border: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
  }
</style>
<article>
  <h2>About</h2>
  <p class="about">
    Hello, Iâ€™m <strong>eden lane</strong>, a frontend engineer.
  </p>
  <p class="about">
    I am a frontend engineer from Russia, Moscow. I have been developing
    websites and apps for more than 7 years. When I switched from C# to
    JavaScript back in 2015, I had a strong belief that web apps are the future.
    
  </p>
  <p class="about">
    Ever since then, I have been trying to make the future closer to people.
  </p>
  <ul class="tags">
    {
      tags.map(tag => (
        <li class="tag" style={{
          backgroundColor: tag.background,
          color: tag.color
        }}>{tag.name}</li>
      ))
    }
  </ul>
  <p class="links">
    <a class="icon" target="_blank" href="https://t.me/eden_lane">
      <img src="/icons/telegram.svg" />
    </a>
    <a class="icon" target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/lane_en">
      <img src="/icons/twitter.svg" />
    </a>
    <a class="icon" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/eden-lane">
      <img src="/icons/github.svg" />
    </a>
  </p>
</article>
